Kinetimancers are force-manipulation practitioners whose tradition synthesizes Necromancer entropy-redirection and Egomancer will-imposition through their shared momentum mechanics. The synthesis was identified theoretically by the Kinetic Formulists — an independent scholarly order not affiliated with either the Psionicist academies or Entropy Scholar networks — who documented that equations describing how will-imposition propagates through cognitive architecture were structurally analogous to equations describing how entropic force propagates through biological systems undergoing dissolution. The Violet Compact's registry scholars, encountering these manuscripts at the Compact's founding, classified the convergence as dangerous theoretical synthesis and applied enhanced monitoring under Section 7 of the Compact's registry provisions — producing the bureaucratic label "Kinetimancer" that became the tradition's name. The momentum doctrine holds that all effective force operates through redirection of existing momentum rather than force generation from nothing: opponents' attacks, environmental processes, cognitive focus vectors, and entropic biological processes all contain momentum that can be redirected toward practitioner objectives. The signature Kinetic Reversion technique reverses incoming force momentum vectors back toward their origin — technically simple in concept, demanding in execution because it requires anticipatory cognitive modeling rather than reactive response. The predictive collapse technique integrates both domains: cognitive modeling identifies optimal moments and vectors for entropy-based momentum redirection, deploying calibrated entropy effects against anticipated responses rather than generic targets. Enhanced monitoring designation in registry records remains an unfulfilled administrative intention because the tradition's practitioners are too few, too independent, and too technically sophisticated for generalist registry assessment.

